, "I took notes of the class discussion." "I kept a list of the words I got wrong."'}, {'id': '004-004', 'name': 'Visualisation', 'description': 'Statements indicating student-initiated efforts to create explanative or organizational drawings to illustrate lesson contents or forming mental images of the material, e.g., "I try to imagine what this would look like."'}], [{'id': '005-001', 'name': 'Teaching and preparing to teach', 'description': 'Statements indicating student-initiated efforts to understand material by explaining it to someone else or preparing to do so, e.g., "I try to explain the material to a friend." "I prepare a presentation for my study group."'}, {'id': '005-002', 'name': 'Self Explanation', 'description': 'Statements indicating student-initiated efforts to understand material by verbally or mentally explaining how new information is related to previously learned material, e.g., "I think out loud when I work through a task."'}], [{'id': '006-001', 'name': 'goal setting and planning', 'description': 'Statements indicating student setting of educational goals or subgoals and planning for prioritising, sequencing, timing, and completing activities related to those goals, e.g., "First, I start studying two weeks before exams, and I pace myself." "I review the materials and decide what to focus on first."'}, {'id': '006-002', 'name': 'Self-evaluating and regulation', 'description': 'Statements indicating student-initiated evaluations of the quality or progress of their work and their own level of understanding, e.g., "I check over my work to make sure I did it right."'}], [{'id': '007-001', 'name': 'Environmental structuring', 'description': 'Statements indicating student-initiated efforts to select or arrange the physical setting to make learning easier, e.g., "I isolate myself so I can concentrate on what I am doing." "I tidy my desk so there is no clutter that distracts me."'}, {'id': '007-002', 'name': 'Self-consequences (i.e. self-rewarding and self-punishment)', 'description': 'Statements indicating student arrangement or imagination of rewards or punishment for success or failure, e.g., "If I do well on a test, I treat myself to a movie."'}, {'id': '007-003', 'name': 'Seeking social assistance from fellow students, teachers or others', 'description': 'Statements indicating student-initiated efforts to solicit help from fellow students, e.g., "If I have problems with math assignments, I ask for help in the class forums." "I ask my classmates/friends" "I find that I get to the correct answer quicker in a study group"'}, {'id': '007-004', 'name': 'Seeking and selecting information', 'description': 'Statements indicating student-initiated efforts to secure further task information from nonsocial sources when undertaking an assignment, e.g., "Before beginning to write the paper, I go to the library to get as much information as possible concerning the topic." "I look for materials online."'}, {'id': '007-005', 'name': 'Time and attention management', 'description': 'Statements indicating student-initiated efforts to structure their work periods and break times taking into account other commitments, motivation and focus, e.g., "I use the Pomodoro Technique to intersperse work periods with short breaks." "I commit to regular study times" "When I can\'t focus I go for a walk and get back to studying after."'}], [{'id': '008-001', 'name': 'other', 'description': 'Statements indicating learning behaviour that is initiated by other persons such as teachers or parents, and all unclear verbal responses, e.g., "I just do what the teacher says."'}]]. Explain which one and why. If you cannot recognise a clear strategy from their answer, explain why and state what additional information would be required to decide if they are using one of the strategies. State 'completed' at the end of your message if you have enough information to categorise the strategy and 'in_progress' if not.
